        <div class="hacker-task-description">
            <p><strong>Task Description:</strong></p>
            <p>Transform an N×N matrix by replacing zero elements with the nearest non-zero element, while leaving equidistant zeros unchanged. The program should handle various input sizes and formats.</p>
        </div>


        <div class="hacker-task-instructions">
            <p><strong>Instructions:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Prepare an input text file with the size of the matrix followed by its elements.</li>
                <li>Input should be in plain text format with properly structured data.</li>
                <li>Ensure the file paths for input and output are correctly specified.</li>
                <li>Check the input data for accuracy to prevent processing errors.</li>
                <li>Execute the application to output the modified matrix.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

